---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SOCIAL_LINKS } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-20">
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 sm:text-5xl">
        Turkdogan Tasdelen
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Senior Software Engineer
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Building software, writing about it, and sharing what I learn along the way.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex gap-4">
        {SOCIAL_LINKS.map(({ name, url }) => (
          <a
            href={url}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm font-medium text-accent hover:underline"
          >
            {name}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-t border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
        About Me
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        <p>
          I have over 15 years of experience as a software engineer, working across small startups and large organizations. Throughout my career I've designed and shipped systems ranging from defense platforms to enterprise-scale data applications and cloud-native microservices. My core expertise is on the JVM — Java and Kotlin — but I'm comfortable picking up whatever the problem demands.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most of my career has been spent at the intersection of hands-on coding and technical leadership. I've led cross-functional teams, shaped system architectures, and mentored engineers — while staying close to the code. I believe the best technical decisions come from people who still build things every day.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm particularly interested in distributed systems, event-driven architectures, and cloud infrastructure on AWS. I've built and operated services using Lambda, SNS, SQS, DynamoDB, and other managed services, and I enjoy the challenge of making complex systems reliable and observable.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of work, I explored deep learning during a Ph.D. program and continue to follow developments in machine learning. I'm a runner, a weight lifter, and a firm believer in continuous improvement — in code and in life. This site is where I share what I learn, the projects I work on, and the occasional opinion on how we build software.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
